Probably, the bug is here.
the following is test case: ./getpid1 -r300 -c3
	case 3:
		populate_all(0, 1);
		pid = get_pid(0);
		printf("new pid: %d\n", pid);
		tsk = find_task_by_pid(400);
		del_task(tsk);
		pid = get_pid(0);
		printf("new pid: %d\n", pid);
		break;
result,
	new pid: 0
	new pid: 1
